rComments: Hare is a legend. He is the best economics professor out there - clear and fair. Tests what you learned, and teaches well. Not patient with stupid questions (understandable), and if you show you've done your work before asking he's very helpful. Overall, deserves the legendary reviews he has got over 48 years of teaching!

His tests are very fair but he seems to hate taking questions from students. One time he I went up to him to ask him a couple of questions after class, he answered the first one quickly, than refused to answer the second question. I was obviously not aware of any rule where I'm only entitled to ask a single question!
